---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
import SectionHeader from '../../components/SectionHeader.astro';
import PullQuote from '../../components/PullQuote.astro';
import Annotation from '../../components/Annotation.astro';
---
<Base title="Against Real-Time" section={6}>
  <SectionHeader n={6} title="Against Real-Time" meta="~400w · interactive" />

  <div class="prose">

    <p>
      Live-updating data is usually theatre. The refresh animation signals vigilance.
      The blinking number signals importance. The "last updated 3 seconds ago" timestamp
      tells you someone cares enough to keep the pipeline warm. Almost none of this serves
      any business decision.
    </p>

    <p>
      Real-time is a feature that serves anxiety, not decisions. The number ticking up
      during a product launch creates the feeling of participation — you are watching
      something happen, you are close to it, you are in the room. But watching a number
      tick is not the same as understanding a trend, and it is certainly not the same
      as making a decision. You would make exactly the same decision — or non-decision —
      if you had looked once per hour. The live feed is not adding information. It is
      adding stimulation.
    </p>

    <PullQuote>
      <p>Real-time is a feature that serves anxiety, not decisions. Almost no business
      decision requires data fresher than an hour.</p>
    </PullQuote>

    <p>
      There are genuine use cases for real-time data. Infrastructure monitoring, where
      a five-minute lag between an incident and an alert is operationally unacceptable.
      Financial trading, where seconds matter. Patient monitoring in clinical settings.
      These are characterised by a specific property: the time-to-decision is shorter than
      the data staleness that would cause a bad decision. Outside those contexts, the case
      for real-time collapses almost entirely.
    </p>

    <p>
      What replaces real-time is not worse data — it is calmer data. A daily summary
      contains the same signal as a live feed, presented without the noise of moment-to-moment
      fluctuation. It is easier to read. It is easier to act on. It does not trigger the
      cortisol response that a pulsing red number at the edge of your vision triggers all day.
    </p>

    <Annotation label="The cost nobody measures">
      Real-time dashboards impose a continuous attention tax. Every time a number updates
      in your peripheral vision, your brain checks it. Multiply that by eight hours,
      by a team of ten, and you are paying an enormous cognitive cost for data that
      almost never changes your decisions.
    </Annotation>

    <p>
      The interactive below places the same data side by side. On the left, a live-updating
      counter with the full theatre of real-time BI. On the right, a calm daily summary
      with context. Same information. Different feeling.
    </p>

  </div>

  <!-- Interactive: Real-Time Theatre -->
  <div class="rt-comparison">
    <!-- LEFT: Live / wrong -->
    <div class="rt-panel rt-panel--cold">
      <div class="rt-panel-chrome">
        <span class="rt-live-dot" id="rt-dot"></span>
        <span>LIVE</span>
        <span class="rt-timestamp" id="rt-timestamp">Updated just now</span>
      </div>
      <div class="rt-panel-body">
        <div class="rt-label-cold">Active Sessions</div>
        <div class="rt-number-cold" id="rt-live-number">4,812</div>
        <div class="rt-sparkline-cold">
          <svg id="rt-spark" viewBox="0 0 200 40" preserveAspectRatio="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
            <polyline id="rt-spark-line" fill="none" stroke="var(--cold-accent)" stroke-width="1.5" points=""/>
          </svg>
        </div>
        <div class="rt-sub-cold">↑ 2.3% vs last hour</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- RIGHT: Calm / right -->
    <div class="rt-panel rt-panel--warm">
      <div class="rt-panel-chrome-warm">Daily Summary</div>
      <div class="rt-panel-body">
        <div class="rt-label-warm">Active Sessions</div>
        <div class="rt-number-warm">~4,800</div>
        <div class="rt-context-row">
          <span class="rt-ctx-item rt-ctx-ok">↑ 8% vs last week</span>
          <span class="rt-ctx-item">Avg 4,650 / day (30d)</span>
        </div>
        <div class="rt-bar-chart">
          <div class="rt-bar-row">
            <span class="rt-day">Mon</span>
            <div class="rt-bar-track"><div class="rt-bar-fill" style="width:72%"></div></div>
            <span class="rt-bar-val">4,320</span>
          </div>
          <div class="rt-bar-row">
            <span class="rt-day">Tue</span>
            <div class="rt-bar-track"><div class="rt-bar-fill" style="width:80%"></div></div>
            <span class="rt-bar-val">4,680</span>
          </div>
          <div class="rt-bar-row">
            <span class="rt-day">Wed</span>
            <div class="rt-bar-track"><div class="rt-bar-fill" style="width:76%"></div></div>
            <span class="rt-bar-val">4,510</span>
          </div>
          <div class="rt-bar-row">
            <span class="rt-day">Thu</span>
            <div class="rt-bar-track"><div class="rt-bar-fill" style="width:85%"></div></div>
            <span class="rt-bar-val">4,930</span>
          </div>
          <div class="rt-bar-row rt-bar-row--today">
            <span class="rt-day">Today</span>
            <div class="rt-bar-track"><div class="rt-bar-fill rt-bar-fill--today" style="width:82%"></div></div>
            <span class="rt-bar-val">4,812</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="rt-calm-note">Updated daily at 9am. Nothing unusual.</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="prose">
    <p>
      The calm version contains more information. You can see the weekly trend,
      the daily average, and whether today is unusual. The live version contains
      more noise. Both show the same 4,800-ish number. Only one of them is doing work.
    </p>
  </div>

</Base>

<style>
  .rt-comparison {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: var(--sp-4);
    margin: var(--sp-8) 0;
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
  }

  @media (max-width: 560px) {
    .rt-comparison { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
  }

  /* Cold / live panel */
  .rt-panel--cold {
    background: var(--cold-bg-0);
    border: 1px solid var(--cold-border);
    border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
    overflow: hidden;
  }

  .rt-panel-chrome {
    background: var(--cold-bg-1);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--cold-border);
    padding: var(--sp-2) var(--sp-4);
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: var(--sp-2);
    font-size: var(--text-caption);
    color: var(--cold-text-3);
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    font-weight: 500;
  }

  .rt-live-dot {
    width: 6px;
    height: 6px;
    background: var(--cold-pulse);
    border-radius: 50%;
    animation: blink 1.2s ease-in-out infinite;
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }

  @keyframes blink {
    0%, 100% { opacity: 1; }
    50% { opacity: 0.2; }
  }

  .rt-timestamp {
    font-size: 10px;
    color: var(--cold-text-3);
    margin-left: auto;
    font-weight: 400;
  }

  .rt-panel-body {
    padding: var(--sp-4) var(--sp-4) var(--sp-6);
  }

  .rt-label-cold {
    font-size: var(--text-caption);
    color: var(--cold-text-3);
    letter-spacing: 0.06em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    margin-bottom: var(--sp-2);
  }

  .rt-number-cold {
    font-size: 32px;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--cold-text);
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    line-height: 1;
    margin-bottom: var(--sp-3);
    font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums;
    transition: color var(--dur-fast);
  }

  .rt-sparkline-cold {
    height: 40px;
    margin-bottom: var(--sp-2);
  }

  .rt-sparkline-cold svg {
    width: 100%;
    height: 100%;
    display: block;
  }

  .rt-sub-cold {
    font-size: var(--text-caption);
    color: var(--cold-green);
  }

  /* Warm / calm panel */
  .rt-panel--warm {
    background: var(--paper-0);
    border: 1px dashed var(--ink-100);
    border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
    overflow: hidden;
  }

  .rt-panel-chrome-warm {
    background: var(--paper-1);
    border-bottom: var(--border-subtle);
    padding: var(--sp-2) var(--sp-4);
    font-size: var(--text-caption);
    color: var(--ink-300);
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    font-weight: 500;
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }

  .rt-label-warm {
    font-size: var(--text-caption);
    color: var(--ink-300);
    letter-spacing: 0.04em;
    margin-bottom: var(--sp-2);
  }

  .rt-number-warm {
    font-size: 32px;
    font-weight: 400;
    color: var(--ink-900);
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    line-height: 1;
    margin-bottom: var(--sp-3);
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
  }

  .rt-context-row {
    display: flex;
    gap: var(--sp-3);
    margin-bottom: var(--sp-4);
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }

  .rt-ctx-item {
    font-size: 11px;
    color: var(--ink-300);
    background: var(--paper-1);
    border-radius: var(--radius-sm);
    padding: 2px 6px;
  }

  .rt-ctx-ok { color: var(--terra-400); }

  /* Bar chart */
  .rt-bar-chart {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 5px;
    margin-bottom: var(--sp-4);
  }

  .rt-bar-row {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: var(--sp-2);
  }

  .rt-day {
    font-size: 10px;
    color: var(--ink-300);
    width: 32px;
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }

  .rt-bar-row--today .rt-day {
    color: var(--terra-400);
    font-weight: 500;
  }

  .rt-bar-track {
    flex: 1;
    height: 8px;
    background: var(--paper-2);
    border-radius: 2px;
    overflow: hidden;
  }

  .rt-bar-fill {
    height: 100%;
    background: var(--paper-3);
    border-radius: 2px;
    transition: width var(--dur-slow) var(--ease-out);
  }

  .rt-bar-fill--today {
    background: var(--terra-300);
  }

  .rt-bar-val {
    font-size: 10px;
    color: var(--ink-300);
    min-width: 34px;
    text-align: right;
    font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums;
  }

  .rt-calm-note {
    font-size: 11px;
    color: var(--ink-100);
    font-style: italic;
  }
</style>

<script>
  // Simulate the "live" left panel flickering with noise
  const liveNum = document.getElementById('rt-live-number') as HTMLElement;
  const rtDot = document.getElementById('rt-dot') as HTMLElement;
  const rtTimestamp = document.getElementById('rt-timestamp') as HTMLElement;
  const sparkLine = document.getElementById('rt-spark-line') as SVGPolylineElement;

  let base = 4812;
  const history: number[] = Array.from({ length: 30 }, (_, i) => {
    return base + Math.round(Math.sin(i * 0.4) * 120 + (Math.random() - 0.5) * 80);
  });

  function sparkPoints() {
    const w = 200, h = 40;
    const min = Math.min(...history);
    const max = Math.max(...history);
    const range = max - min || 1;
    return history.map((v, i) => {
      const x = (i / (history.length - 1)) * w;
      const y = h - ((v - min) / range) * (h - 4) - 2;
      return `${x.toFixed(1)},${y.toFixed(1)}`;
    }).join(' ');
  }

  function update() {
    const delta = Math.round((Math.random() - 0.48) * 30);
    base = Math.max(4200, Math.min(5400, base + delta));
    history.shift();
    history.push(base);
    liveNum.textContent = base.toLocaleString();
    sparkLine.setAttribute('points', sparkPoints());
    rtTimestamp.textContent = 'Updated just now';
  }

  sparkLine.setAttribute('points', sparkPoints());

  setInterval(update, 1800);
</script>
